x_1,x_2, \dots ,x_n \geq 0 
 x_1 + x_2 + \dots + x_n \leq \frac{1}{2} \implies (1-x_1)(1-x_2) \cdots (1-x_n) \geq \frac{1}{2}
(1-a)(1-b) \geq 1-(a+b)
(1-x_1)(1-x_2)...(1-x_n) \geq 1-(x_1+x_2+...+x_n)
(1-x_1)(1-x_2)...(1-x_n)(1-x_{n+1}) \geq  \left[ 1-(x_1+x_2+...+x_n) \right] (1-x_{n+1}) \geq  1-(x_1+x_2+...+x_n+x_{n+1})
1-x_i \geq 0
x_1+..+x_n \leq \frac{1}{2}
n=1
x_1 \le \frac 12 \implies 1-x_1 \ge \frac 12
